Warm the oil in a Dutch oven set over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 3 to 5 minutes, or until the onion is soft. Add the broth, tomatoes (with juice), beans, and pasta. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes, or until the pasta is cooked. Add the Swiss chard or spinach and salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 minutes, or until the chard or spinach is wilted.